# SQL Migration Convention

Any time a code change requires a new or altered database column, table, constraint, index, or RLS policy, create a dedicated `.sql` file in the `supabase/` folder.

## Rules

- One migration per file. Name the file after what it does (e.g., `caution-column.sql`, `progress-log-stage-check.sql`).
- Include a short comment at the top explaining the purpose and expected shape.
- Use `IF NOT EXISTS` / `IF EXISTS` where safe to make migrations re-runnable.
- Never bundle unrelated schema changes into one file.
- If dropping and recreating a constraint, put both statements in one file.

## Example

```sql
-- Add fulfillment_phase to jobs for SHIP page state tracking.
-- Values: awaiting_instructions | ready_pickup | ready_ship | local_pickup | in_house | held | shipped
ALTER TABLE jobs ADD COLUMN IF NOT EXISTS fulfillment_phase text;
```
